<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14401.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">NHS 24</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14401.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80310" speakername="Ross Finnie (West of Scotland) (LD)" spid="S3W-14401" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what the costs were of setting up <a href="http://www.nhs24.com" target="_blank">www.nhs24.com</a> .</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14401.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80396" speakername="Nicola Sturgeon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>The initial costs of establishing NHS24.com were not recorded separately by NHS 24 as they were included within a number of infrastructure and application developments.</p>

  <p>However, as part of an on-going process to improve public accessibility to NHS 24 services, the website was redesigned in 2007 at a cost of &pound;36,687.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14402.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">NHS 24</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14402.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80310" speakername="Ross Finnie (West of Scotland) (LD)" spid="S3W-14402" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what the monthly costs have been of <a href="http://www.nhs24.com" target="_blank">www.nhs24.com</a> in each month since its inception.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14402.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80396" speakername="Nicola Sturgeon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>This information is not recorded by month. However, the annual maintenance cost of the website for 2007-08 was &pound;7,200. This covers technical support, server and database monitoring, uploads, creation/modification of page designs including images and the development of content management.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14403.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">NHS 24</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14403.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80310" speakername="Ross Finnie (West of Scotland) (LD)" spid="S3W-14403" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive which telephone operating company has the contract for NHS 24 and when the contract will be due for renewal.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14403.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80396" speakername="Nicola Sturgeon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">

  <p>I refer the member to the answer to question S3W-14264 on 24 June 2008. All answers to written parliamentary questions are available on the Parliament&rsquo;s website, the search facility for which can be found at <a href="../../../webapp/wa.search">http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/webapp/wa.search</a> .</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-07-07.S3W-14404.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa0707.htm#2">NHS 24</minor-heading>

